==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Arion
<hw>Arion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>In Greek legend,
a fabulous horse, the offspring of Poseidon by Demeter (or, in other
accounts, Gaea or a harpy) who to escape him had metamorphosed herself
into a mare. It was successively owned by Copreus, Oncus, Heracles, and
Adrastus. It possessed marvelous powers of speech, and its right feet
were those of a man.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Century Dict. 1906</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ariose</ent>⟦br⟧
